cs.NE, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as the Dendritic Cell algorithm is inspired by biological neural networks and the paper discusses its use as an anomaly detector. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also likely as the paper specifically applies the DCA to computer security. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the DCA is a machine learning algorithm. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the influence of signal selection on the behavior of the algorithm. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the DCA can be seen as a control system for detecting anomalies.
